Rating: 4
Made this dish (modified) for Mother's Day brunch and it was a big hit in our family. I did make it with the following modifications and it was still very good: 2 T. oil instead of 2 T. butter + 1 T. oil; 1/2 package frozen Ore-Ida shredded hash browns (approx 3/4 lb total I would estimate); 3 Tbsp plain fat-free yogurt instead of sour cream; wasabi instead of horseradish; 2 T. capers instead of 3 T.; 4 oz Scottish smoked salmon (because I couldn't find a bigger package!). Also, did not serve with poached eggs on top, but instead served it alongside omelettes and waffles. Using shredded hash browns brought down the cooking time significantly (looking at other cooks' notes) and we liked that texture. Despite these changes, the dish was still delicious! I would definitely make this again.

